      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's the revised email:\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed by your exceptional skills in system design and your alignment with our company culture. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience with our specific cloud stack aligns more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely excited about the prospect of having you join our team. Your passion for system design and commitment to delivering high-quality solutions are truly admirable, and we have no doubt that you will excel in your future endeavors. We're also keeping your resume on file, and if we have any future openings that align with your skills and interests, we'd be happy to reach out to you again.\n\nWe appreciate the time and effort you invested in our interview process, and we're grateful for the opportunity to have met you. If you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out to me directly.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nBy adding the sentence about keeping their resume on file, you're leaving the door open for potential future opportunities and showing that",
